{ UID: uid-080a-9478-a5d5-ce76
  is: article
  title: "Start Here!"
  text: "You probably don't want loads of intro waffle, so let's get started right away.."
        "On the right, you see two views of what are called 'objects' in Cyrus."
        "The middle panel has the raw Cyrus 'code', and the right panel has the resulting 'render'."
        "The object is an 'editable gui' - this tells the browser code how to render it and that you can try and edit it"
        "The gui's 'view' has the word 'Hello' - so that's what you see!"
        "Type 'World!' after that 'Hello' in the middle panel. Then hit 'Update' below it."
        "The far panel should update accordingly. Hit refresh if it doesn't for some reason."
}

{ UID: uid-419a-bc8d-d4ff-4146
  is: article
  title: "Rewriting, '=>' or 'becomes'"
  text: "Let's get the computer to add 'World!' for us."
        "Paste the following code in:"
        "|["
        "{"
        "  Rules:{"
        "    is: gui rule"
        "  }"
        "  is: editable gui"
        "  view: Hello"
        "}"
        "]|"
        "This adds 'Rules' to the object. We have the beginnings of a 'gui rule'. A rule has to say it 'is' a rule, and what it's a rule for."
        "Now add the bit that does the rewrite:"
        "|["
        "{"
        "  Rules:{"
        "    is: gui rule"
        "    ![view: Hello => Hello World]!"
        "  }"
        "  is: editable gui"
        "  view: Hello"
        "}"
        "]|"
        "This is a rule that says 'when you see 'Hello' in the 'view:' of the object, rewrite it to 'Hello World'"
        "Another way of reading it is 'view Hello ![becomes]! Hello World'"
        "A rule does its best to match, and if it matches, the rewrites are performed"
        "Hit 'Update', then refresh. What happened? You should see 'Hello,World Hello'. It's our first 'bug'!"
}

